pddl.prompt:
You are the orchestrator. You will receive the ordered primitive moves from the three agents:
{moves_agent_1}
{moves_agent_2}
{moves_agent_3}
Your task:
1) Verify that the concatenation/interleaving of these moves can form a legal Tower of Hanoi execution adhering to disk-move permissions and the rule that a larger disk cannot be placed on a smaller disk.
2) If conflicts or illegal moves appear, indicate the conflict and propose adjustments to the per-agent sequences to resolve them while preserving agent restrictions.
3) Produce a final, fully ordered single-list plan of primitive moves in the format 'agent_i: move disk X from peg1 to peg2'.
4) Emit a PDDL domain and PDDL problem suitable for FastDownwards that models the instance (10 disks A..J, pegs left/middle/right), encodes agent move restrictions, initial state, and goal state, and is consistent with the integrated move plan. Enclose the PDDL domain between <domain> and </domain> and the PDDL problem between <problem> and </problem>.
